raw_data.title: Technical Director 2
raw_data.description: Applies technical expertise to assist in defining, analyzing, validating, and documenting complex operating environments, states of technology, and current engineering processes. Conducts complex technical investigations through advanced research techniques, analysis, or development phases of information technology engineering projects.  Responsible for the software development or engineering systems and/or sub-systems while considering security impacts within the entire System Development Life Cycle (SDLC) process.

raw_data.title: Technical Director
raw_data.description: A technical lead for the contract effort, serves as a primary technical interface and point of contact with Government program authorities and representatives on technical issues. Establishes system information requirements in the development of enterprise?wide or large?scale information systems, as well as analyzes government and/or customer requirements in support of the information system. Designs/Tests architecture to include the software, hardware, and communications to support the total requirements as well as provide for present and future cross?functional requirements and interfaces.

raw_data.title: Senior Software Developer
raw_data.description: Applies logical analysis for test and evaluation on all programs within a system wide scope. Performs comprehensive analysis of hardware/software concepts, as well as designing and testing requirements. Reviews, analyzes, integrates and conducts test and evaluation of government and/or contractor generated source data and develops interim documentation, requirements, and/or solutions. Performs system wide concept formulation, system design analysis and subsystems design analysis. Responsible for software development of systems and/or sub-systems while considering security impacts within the entire System Development Life Cycle (SDLC) process.

raw_data.title: Software Developer
raw_data.description: Applies logical analysis for test and evaluation on all programs within a system wide scope. Performs comprehensive analysis of hardware/software concepts, as well as designing and testing requirements. Reviews, analyzes, integrates and conducts test and evaluation of government and/or contractor generated source data and develops interim documentation, requirements, and/or solutions. Performs system wide concept formulation, system design analysis and subsystems design analysis. Responsible for supporting software development of systems and/or sub-systems.  Responsible for modules, segments, or phases of the broader or more complex information system.

raw_data.title: Senior Technical Consultant
raw_data.description: Analyzes functional business applications and design specifications for functional activities. Develops block diagrams and logic flow charts. Translates general requests into detailed requirements.  Translates general and/or detailed requirements into design and computer software. Tests, debugs, and refines the software, while collaborating with developers and non-developers to produce the required product. Prepares required documentation, including both program?level and user?level documentation. Enhances software and/or general processes supporting the system to reduce operating time or improve efficiency. Provides technical direction to programmers to ensure program deadlines are met.

raw_data.title: Mid-Level Technical Consultant
raw_data.description: Mid?level Technical Consultants provide specialized knowledge of system requirements and programming specifications. They design and/or document solutions or requirements based on customer needs and technical considerations. They analyze job tasks, organizational structure and user requirements to provide system?wide solutions. They apply analytical expertise to assist in defining, analyzing, validating, and documenting complex operating environments, states of technology, and current processes.

raw_data.title: Information  Security (IA) Security Specialist-Master
raw_data.description: An IA lead for the contract effort, serves as a primary technical interface and point of contact with Government program authorities and representatives on IA inquiries and practices. Establishes information system security requirements in support of enterprise?wide or large?scale information systems, as well as analyzes government and/or customer processes in support of security controls.  Designs and documents system security plans and provides recommendations for implementation, while also supporting Contingency Plans, Configuration Management Plans, and performing Security Assessments over controls that support a given information system.

raw_data.title: Information  Security (IA) Security-Journeyman
raw_data.description: Establishes information system security requirements in support of enterprise?wide or large?scale information systems, as well as analyzes government and/or customer processes in support of security controls.  Designs and documents system security plans and provides recommendations for implementation, while also supporting Contingency Plans, Configuration Management Plans, and performing Security Assessments over controls that support a given information system.

raw_data.title: Information  Security (IA) Security-Entry Level
raw_data.description: Reviews established system security requirements and policies.  Performs an analysis and comparison of existing processes against best practices and NIST requirements.  Supports efforts to establish information system security requirements in support of enterprise?wide or large?scale information systems.  Supports the development of system security plans, contingency plans, configuration management plans, and security assessment documentation.
